      • setParam3

        public void setParam3(double angle)
        The third parameter in the AutoSpreadsheet, angle. The angle is relative to the angle where the robot started. The angle should be close to the current angle of the robot (ie this command is not appropriate for both turning and driving). If the robot needs to turn prior to driving straight, use TurnGyroAbs first.
        Specified by:
        setParam3 in interface AutoSpreadsheetCommand
        Overrides:
        setParam3 in class DriveDistance
        Parameters:
        angle - The angle (in degrees) to maintain while driving
